  "text": "Although the physical appearance of eggs, buoyancy, or ovarian fluid pH measurements provide some clues about the quality of eggs, still the fertilization success and subsequent normal embryonic development remain the most reliable measures of egg quality [CITATION_1] . However, a posteriori quality check is not the ideal measure for the aquaculture industry, as certain resources are allocated to the production process prior to the measure.",
